  "folder": null,
  "name": "Trouble Maker",
  "type": "background",
  "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-writing-letter.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You may come from privilege where you can do no wrong, or from poverty where you can do nothing right.</p><p>Perhaps your parents' busy social schedule means that they pay you little attention or you have no parents and have no solid foundation from the get go and no one would spare you a moment's glance to see what potential might lie undiscovered inside you.</p><p>Regardless, you do not appreciate or accept the gifts of your circumstance, or you reject the curses of your circumstances and you lash out with ostentatious behavior as a means to attract attention to yourself.</p><p>You have always had a way with people.</p><p>You know what makes them tick and you can twist their words into your advantage.</p><p>It's a useful talent, and one that you're perfectly willing to use to get yourself out of trouble.</p><hr /><p><strong>Skill Proficiencies:</strong> Deception, Sleight of Hand</p><p><strong>Tool Proficiencies:</strong> Forgery Kit </p><p><strong>Equipment:</strong> One set of commoners' clothes, a Forgery kit and a wallet containing 100 Ryo.</p><p><strong>Equipment Pack:</strong> Infiltrator's or Traveler's Pack (Choose one).</p><hr /><p><strong>FEATURE: PITIABLE</strong></p><p>People will typically let you get away with social faux pas that might otherwise sour a business deal or incite an aggressive reaction - but they do this out of sheer pity, not because as you suspect, they are beguiled by your wit.</p><hr /><p><strong>BAD INFLUENCE</strong></p><p>Select one:</p><p>• Increase any ability score by +1. (<strong>Recommended:</strong> Strength, Charisma)</p><p>• Gain a feat from Chapter 13: Customization options.</p><p>Regardless of the feat chosen, you do not gain an ability score improvement from the feat you select. (<strong>Recommended:</strong> General, Skill, Chakra)</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
